to get them to make peace.

100
00:07:13,252 --> 00:07:14,872
So that we could be a family again.

101
00:07:15,372 --> 00:07:19,582
But... if Grandpa doesn't want to,
why can't we just leave him alone?

102
00:07:20,082 --> 00:07:22,042
Oh, Mike, never forget this:

103
00:07:22,542 --> 00:07:24,752
your grandfather is
part of this family.

104
00:07:25,252 --> 00:07:28,122
And there's nothing more important
than family.

105
00:07:30,252 --> 00:07:32,872
That's why we can't
give up, alright?

106
00:07:43,502 --> 00:07:45,542
"His grandfather
reinvented the oil industry!"

107
00:07:46,002 --> 00:07:49,002
"His father was the great
visionary of nuclear energy!"

108
00:07:49,502 --> 00:07:52,542
"And today Richard Carson III owns
the biggest energy empire in the world!"

109
00:07:53,042 --> 00:07:54,082
Ladies and gentlemen,

110
00:07:54,502 --> 00:07:57,752
let's welcome Richard Carson
with a big round of applause!

111
00:08:18,002 --> 00:08:19,042
Yeah!

112
00:08:23,872 --> 00:08:26,162
How can <i>that guy</i>
be on TV?

113
00:08:26,622 --> 00:08:28,162
He owns the channel.

114
00:08:32,162 --> 00:08:34,252
What's up babe?
Looking good!

115
00:08:34,702 --> 00:08:35,752
I love you, Carson!

116
00:08:36,042 --> 00:08:37,082
Have it, baby!

117
00:08:37,162 --> 00:08:38,502
Ah!

118
00:08:39,542 --> 00:08:40,832
Oh!

119
00:08:42,162 --> 00:08:43,202
Mr. Carson?

120
00:08:43,752 --> 00:08:45,252
Yeah!

121
00:08:46,122 --> 00:08:47,162
Yeah! Yeah!

122
00:08:47,452 --> 00:08:48,502
Mr. Carson...

123
00:08:49,002 --> 00:08:51,452
Mr. Carson, you were going to
make an announcement.

124
00:08:52,002 --> 00:08:53,662
Of course.

125
00:08:54,162 --> 00:08:56,292
Let's cut to chase.
Did you know that 50%

126
00:08:56,792 --> 00:08:58,292
of the world population

127
00:08:58,792 --> 00:09:00,832
think that men never set foot
on the Moon?

128
00:09:01,332 --> 00:09:03,332
Oh, come on, what's it with this guy?

129
00:09:03,832 --> 00:09:07,002
Yes, there are all kinds of
conspiracy theories

130
00:09:08,662 --> 00:09:11,582
The Moon.
My father's biggest dream.

131
00:09:12,082 --> 00:09:14,202
He offered part of his fortune
to go.

132
00:09:14,752 --> 00:09:17,372
But NASA refused.
My father,

133
00:09:17,872 --> 00:09:19,702
a man that had everything,

134
00:09:20,252 --> 00:09:23,582
died not having been able
to achieve his biggest dream.

135
00:09:24,082 --> 00:09:25,202
Aaawww...

136
00:09:25,752 --> 00:09:27,122
Unfair!

137
00:09:27,622 --> 00:09:28,662
Well, such a mission

138
00:09:28,752 --> 00:09:30,952
requires well-prepared astronauts
, doesn't it?

139
00:09:31,502 --> 00:09:33,162
No! That was their excuse!

140
00:09:33,662 --> 00:09:36,622
But today I'm going to reveal
the truth.

141
00:09:37,122 --> 00:09:41,292
The whole world will know
that the Space Race

142
00:09:41,792 --> 00:09:44,752
was nothing but a big, fat... lie!

143
00:09:48,832 --> 00:09:50,372
"It's an honor...
and a priviledge

144
00:09:50,912 --> 00:09:54,122
to be here today on behalf of
all peaceful men..."

145
00:09:54,622 --> 00:09:56,292
"Ouch!".

146
00:09:58,122 --> 00:09:59,162
"Cut!".

147
00:09:59,412 --> 00:10:01,372
"I want that guy out
right now!"

148
00:10:01,912 --> 00:10:05,912
"Even a trained monkey could do it
much better! I said "cut"!"

149
00:10:06,792 --> 00:10:08,082
Ha! I knew it!

150
00:10:08,582 --> 00:10:10,542
What?! That was fake!

151
00:10:11,082 --> 00:10:13,162
Yeah, right! And how do you know that,
know-it-all?

152
00:10:13,662 --> 00:10:16,502
What are you talking about, idi...?!
- Scott, the children...

153
00:10:17,002 --> 00:10:18,622
And why doesn't NASA
go back to the Moon

154
00:10:19,042 --> 00:10:20,662
and prove that guy's
a liar?

155
00:10:21,162 --> 00:10:23,912
I wish we could, but we don't have
rockets prepared for that now.

156
00:10:24,412 --> 00:10:26,292
The Space Race finished
years ago.

157
00:10:26,792 --> 00:10:30,452
Wow, your father would be
very proud of what you found.

158
00:10:31,002 --> 00:10:33,372
Daddy...
was my everything...

159
00:10:33,872 --> 00:10:37,412
When he died, I asked for his ashes
to be merged with this diamond...

160
00:10:37,912 --> 00:10:40,292
so that he would always
be with me...

161
00:10:41,002 --> 00:10:45,542
And I swore that I would do
everything in my power to honor his memory.

162
00:10:46,042 --> 00:10:47,412
Aw...

163
00:10:47,912 --> 00:10:49,292
Unfair!

164
00:10:49,832 --> 00:10:52,912
It's time to end this fraud!

165
00:10:54,752 --> 00:10:58,372
I, Richard Carson III, will be
the first man to set foot...

166
00:10:58,872 --> 00:11:00,872
on the Moon!

167
00:11:15,622 --> 00:11:19,502
Look, daddy, he does have a rocket!
- Tess!

168
00:11:22,252 --> 00:11:24,502
Ha! That guy is awesome!

169
00:11:28,002 --> 00:11:29,872
That's for you, dad!

170
00:11:31,502 --> 00:11:34,082
Nonsense!
How can they believe that presumptuous fraud?

171
00:11:34,622 --> 00:11:38,042
We're getting thousands of messages
saying that the trip to the Moon was fake!

172
00:11:38,542 --> 00:11:40,122
Social networks
are on fire!

173
00:11:40,662 --> 00:11:42,372
Everybody speaking about
"the big lie".

174
00:11:42,872 --> 00:11:46,082
Ms. President, we need
to stop this scam!

175
00:11:47,042 --> 00:11:48,952
I was just a little girl
when it happened,

176
00:11:49,502 --> 00:11:52,622
but I remember very well the moment
we set foot on the Moon.

177
00:11:53,162 --> 00:11:55,332
Ms. President,
we have some intel.

178
00:11:55,832 --> 00:11:57,252
Carson intends to claim the Moon

179
00:11:57,662 --> 00:11:58,702
before the United Nations.

180
00:11:59,122 --> 00:12:02,452
Impossible! We put that flag
in the name of mankind!

181
00:12:03,002 --> 00:12:05,582
If he goes and destroys
what's left of the other missions,

182
00:12:06,042 --> 00:12:07,082
including the flag,

183
00:12:07,582 --> 00:12:10,332
the world will believe that he is
the first man on the Moon.

184
00:12:10,832 --> 00:12:14,122
Ms. President,
give me the order and I'll turn him to dust!

185
00:12:14,662 --> 00:12:17,412
Calm down, admiral. Just keep a look
on that man.

186
00:12:17,872 --> 00:12:20,452
We will not let him
rewrite History.

187
00:12:20,952 --> 00:12:22,452
We need to do something. Now!

188
00:12:25,752 --> 00:12:27,002
Pliers.

189
00:12:28,542 --> 00:12:30,252
Screwdriver.

190
00:12:31,332 --> 00:12:33,452
Will we get the flag
with this?

191
00:12:34,002 --> 00:12:35,912
I find your lack of faith
disturbing.

192
00:12:36,412 --> 00:12:37,792
The Marty-Rocket is the best.

193
00:12:38,292 --> 00:12:41,042
Everytime you say that,
something terrible happens.

194
00:12:41,542 --> 00:12:44,752
Quiet, little reporter,
and let the genius work.

195
00:12:45,252 --> 00:12:48,252
Right... How did dinner
with your family go?

196
00:12:48,752 --> 00:12:50,412
Without my grandfather, as usual.

197
00:12:50,912 --> 00:12:52,792
Not cool, what's up with him?

198
00:12:53,332 --> 00:12:54,702
I don't know.

199
00:12:56,002 --> 00:12:57,252
All I know is that

200
00:12:57,752 --> 00:12:58,792
my grandfather was going to

201
00:12:59,002 --> 00:13:02,162
be part of the last mission
to the Moon.

202
00:13:03,332 --> 00:13:05,582
But a few days before
the take off

203
00:13:06,082 --> 00:13:07,502
he was cut off from the mission.

204
00:13:08,002 --> 00:13:09,042
<i>Why?</i>

205
00:13:09,122 --> 00:13:10,162
He wouldn't tell anyone.

206
00:13:10,452 --> 00:13:13,042
He just got away
from the world.

207
00:13:13,542 --> 00:13:16,372
And one day, he left
his own home.

208
00:13:16,872 --> 00:13:19,872
And my father never understood why.
Since then,

209
00:13:20,372 --> 00:13:22,252
they barely
speak to each other.

210
00:13:22,752 --> 00:13:26,042
My mother is doing everything she can
to reunite them to no avail.

211
00:13:26,542 --> 00:13:29,542
Look at the bright side! I used to have
a good six pack.

212
00:13:30,042 --> 00:13:31,542
And now...
it's one big can.

213
00:13:32,042 --> 00:13:34,582
All thanks to my grandparents,
that won't stop giving me sweets.

214
00:13:35,082 --> 00:13:38,332
I don't care anymore. It's always been
like this in my family.

215
00:13:39,002 --> 00:13:40,792
Uh! Hold that.

216
00:13:41,372 --> 00:13:45,252
How can you not care? Don't say that.
You don't know what you are missing.

217
00:13:45,752 --> 00:13:47,752
I have my grandparents,
my nine siblings...

218
00:13:48,252 --> 00:13:50,912
my uncles, my cousins,
my second cousins...

219
00:13:51,412 --> 00:13:53,332
Wow, are you guys a family or
an entire country?

220
00:13:53,832 --> 00:13:55,582
Shut up, Carrothead!

221
00:13:56,082 --> 00:13:58,582
Seriously, don't give up.
You should do something about it.

222
00:13:59,082 --> 00:14:01,332
You don't get it.
I can't do anything.

223
00:14:01,832 --> 00:14:04,372
Nothing? You only need to
get them to talk.

224
00:14:04,872 --> 00:14:06,912
Yeah, right. So easy...

225
00:14:07,412 --> 00:14:10,162
Ok, who cares, right?
You are such a chicken.

226
00:14:10,662 --> 00:14:11,702
Hey, I'm not a chicken!

227
00:14:11,952 --> 00:14:13,002
Of course not...

228
00:14:13,082 --> 00:14:14,792
You are the king of chickens!

229
00:14:16,042 --> 00:14:17,542
Ah! Igor!

230
00:14:18,042 --> 00:14:20,252
See, genius? Disaster...

231
00:14:22,252 --> 00:14:23,452
Scott!

232
00:14:24,002 --> 00:14:25,832
Scott! Scott!

233
00:14:26,912 --> 00:14:28,622
Just what's my father doing here?

234
00:14:29,082 --> 00:14:31,792
Scott! Scott! We're going back!
- Wait, what?

235
00:14:32,252 --> 00:14:33,622
National priority.

236
00:14:34,082 --> 00:14:37,162
Orders from the President.
- What are you talking about, Jack?

237
00:14:37,662 --> 00:14:39,792
Sam, Scott,
we're going back to the Moon!

238
00:14:40,292 --> 00:14:42,002
And you will be the commander!

239
00:14:47,792 --> 00:14:49,252
The mission's as follows:
get to the Moon

240
00:14:49,702 --> 00:14:51,582
before Carson
destroys the flag

241
00:14:52,042 --> 00:14:53,082
that was put there in 1969.

242
00:14:53,372 --> 00:14:55,582
If there's no flag, people'll
believe we were never there.

243
00:14:56,082 --> 00:14:59,582
Wow! The Moon,
a Goldwing on the Moon...

244
00:15:00,082 --> 00:15:01,122
Wait...

245
00:15:01,332 --> 00:15:02,702
And how are we
going to go?

246
00:15:03,252 --> 00:15:05,292
Does the name Saturn V
ring a bell?

247
00:15:05,792 --> 00:15:07,872
Are you kidding? That old piece of junk
from the NASA museum?

248
00:15:08,332 --> 00:15:09,372
Bingo!

249
00:15:09,662 --> 00:15:10,702
They're going to repair it.

250
00:15:10,752 --> 00:15:11,792
Saturn V...

251
00:15:11,872 --> 00:15:14,122
The biggest rocket
ever built.

252
00:15:14,582 --> 00:15:19,002
It's going to fly again after 45 years.
We'll take off in a month.

253
00:15:19,542 --> 00:15:22,872
A month?! - Impossible!
No one in NASA

254
00:15:23,372 --> 00:15:25,662
knows how to pilot that relic.
- They've asked some former

255
00:15:26,162 --> 00:15:28,412
NASA astronauts for help,
they'll train us.

256
00:15:28,912 --> 00:15:32,952
Well, I know somebody who's not
going to care anyway.

257
00:15:33,452 --> 00:15:34,912
You know your father.

258
00:15:35,412 --> 00:15:37,622
It's the only one who refused to come.

259
00:15:38,162 --> 00:15:40,952
This is your chance, chicken.

260
00:15:41,502 --> 00:15:44,332
Ok, guys, we've got
a mission.

261
00:15:45,832 --> 00:15:47,792
We need to bring this
to my grandfather.

262
00:15:48,292 --> 00:15:50,872
The veterans are coming tomorrow
and he needs to be there.

263
00:15:51,372 --> 00:15:52,502
Why don't you give him a call?

264
00:15:53,002 --> 00:15:54,042
He won't pick up the phone.

265
00:15:54,412 --> 00:15:55,542
What about an email?

266
00:15:55,792 --> 00:15:57,372
He doesn't have a computer.

267
00:16:22,042 --> 00:16:24,292
Come on, guys!
And remember: failure...

268
00:16:24,792 --> 00:16:25,832
